# --- Local reference material — deliberately NOT committed ---
# The official D&D 5E rulebook PDFs live in this folder so Claude / Cowork can
# read them as reference and inspiration. They are COPYRIGHTED and this repo is
# PUBLIC, so they must never be pushed to GitHub (that would republish them),
# and 600+ MB of binaries would permanently bloat the repo. They stay safe on
# your local machine only. (See DECISIONS.md, 2026-07-07.)
*.pdf

# --- Campaign content — deliberately NOT committed ---
# Story beats, encounters, NPCs, creatures and session notes for the live game.
# This repo is PUBLIC and deploys to GitHub Pages, so publishing these would
# spoil the campaign for the very players who use the site. `dm.html` itself
# ships, but it is EMPTY for anyone who isn't the DM: their browser has no saved
# workspace, and campaign/manifest.json simply 404s. That 404 — not the passcode
# on dm.html — is the real protection. (See DECISIONS.md, 2026-07-08.)
#
# Never `git add -f` a file in here "just as an example". One slip and the
# campaign is in public git history forever.
campaign/

# OS / editor junk
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store
*~
